						<summary>

						<p>On the north face of the north pillar in the rock-cut shrine in the Mēlaikōyil temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in characters of about the 11th century records the gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by a private individual for burning a perpetual lamp and for feeding five Brāhmaṇas during the seven days of Paṅguṉi-Uttiram to the deity Tirumūlaṭṭāṉattu Perumāṉaḍigaḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
